@lorendias 

> I would like to see Nautilus Desktop decoupled and become a Gnome Shell Extension.

Why Shell Extension? Shell extension are written with gnome javascript where Nautilus is C. Desktop functionality has already been decoupled. It's all about packaging it as a separate binary. User will install it as a nautilus extension. It's as simple as that. Why go through the trouble of converting already decoupled c code into javascript?

